Add platform-bus NIC support for VPP via AF_XDP.

NXP DPAA1 FMan Ethernet NICs (driver: fsl_dpa) are on the platform bus,
not PCI. VPP's default path hardcodes driver='dpdk' for all interfaces,
which crashes on platform-bus NICs. This patch:

1. Adds fsl_dpa to SUPPORTED_DRIVERS and not_pci_drv lists
2. Introduces platform_bus_xdp_drivers list for auto-detection
3. Auto-selects driver='xdp' for platform-bus NICs with XDP defaults
4. Enables af_xdp_plugin.so and conditionally disables dpdk_plugin.so
5. Lowers resource minimums for embedded ARM64 boards (2 CPUs, 256M heap)

Tested on NXP LS1046A Mono Gateway with VPP v25.10.0-48 AF_XDP on
eth3/eth4 (10G SFP+).

--- a/src/conf_mode/vpp.py
